# Shopify Theme Coding Standards

## Liquid
- Use `{% liquid %}` for multiline logic blocks
- Use `{% render %}` never `{% include %}`
- Use `| image_url: width: N` never `| img_url`
- Use `{% comment %}` or `{% # %}` for comments
- Server-side render with Liquid first; use JS only when necessary
- Use `| t` for all user-facing text (locale translations)
- Scope variables with `{% capture %}` to avoid polluting global scope

## CSS
- BEM naming: `.block__element--modifier` with dashes between words
- Max specificity `0 4 0` (four classes). Prefer `0 1 0` (single class)
- Never use IDs as selectors
- Never use `!important` â€” if unavoidable, comment why
- CSS variables for all values; never hardcode colors
- Mobile-first (`min-width` media queries)
- No nesting beyond first level (exception: media queries, parent-state children)
- No `&` operator in nesting

## JavaScript
- No external dependencies; use native browser APIs first
- `const` over `let`; never `var`
- Module pattern with `#` private methods
- `for...of` over `.forEach()`
- Use `<details>`/`<summary>`, `popover` over JS toggles
- Blank line before new code blocks (anything with `{` `}`)

## HTML
- Semantic elements (`<nav>`, `<main>`, `<article>`, `<section>`, `<aside>`)
- CamelCase IDs, append `-{{ section.id }}` or `-{{ block.id }}`
- All interactive elements must be focusable
- Use `tabindex="0"` only (never positive values)
- Proper ARIA labels and roles on custom controls
- `loading="lazy"` below fold; `fetchpriority="high"` on LCP images

## Schema Settings
- Order settings to match visual order (top-to-bottom, left-to-right)
- Resource pickers first, then customization settings
- Group related settings under headings (Layout, Typography, Colors, Padding)
- Checkbox labels as nouns not verbs ("Language selector" not "Enable language selector")
- Always provide sensible `default` values
